at each emitting vibrational level v’ yielded the (Δv=2)/(Δv=1) Einstein coefficient
ratios for v’=2–13. The results provide comparisons to previous theoretical and
experimental data, and reflect the behavior of the dipole moment function for NO(X 2Π).
The measured ratios indicate an overtone Einstein coefficient A2,0=0.94±0.11 s−1
for an assumed fundamental value A1,0=13.4 s−1.},
DOI = {10.1063/1.462407}
